## Standard Output Format

```markdown
Status: Done

# Implementation for Error Modal

## Files Created

- `src/components/modal/ErrorModal/ErrorModal.tsx` ✅
- `src/components/modal/ErrorModal/ErrorModal.module.scss` ✅
- `src/components/modal/ErrorModal/index.ts` ✅
- `src/services/errorModalService.ts` ✅

## Files Modified

- `src/services/api/axiosInstance.ts` ✅
- `src/components/modal/index.ts` ✅

## Files Deleted

None

## Implementation Summary

### What Was Done

Created ErrorModal component following the modal pattern from COMPONENTS.md. Implemented errorModalService as singleton to manage modal state. Added axios interceptor to catch API errors and display them via the modal.

### Key Components/Functions

- **ErrorModal** – Displays error title and message with close button
- **errorModalService** – Singleton service with show(error) and hide() methods
- **axiosErrorInterceptor** – Catches 4xx/5xx and triggers errorModalService

### Type Definitions Created

- `ErrorModalPropsT` – Component props (title, message, onClose)
- `ApiErrorT` – Error shape from API (status, message, details)

### Integration Points

- ErrorModal uses base Modal component from Components/modal
- errorModalService uses React context for rendering
- Interceptor added to shared axios instance

## Checks Performed

### Prettier Formatting

✅ All modified files formatted with Prettier

Files formatted:
- src/components/modal/ErrorModal/ErrorModal.tsx
- src/components/modal/ErrorModal/ErrorModal.module.scss
- src/services/errorModalService.ts

### TypeScript

✅ tsc --noEmit - no errors

### ESLint

✅ yarn lint passed

Warnings found:
- src/services/errorModalService.ts:12 - prefer-const (minor)

## Environment Variables Needed

None

## Notes for Tester

### What to Test

1. Trigger API error (e.g., invalid login) → modal appears
2. Click close button → modal closes
3. Press Escape → modal closes
4. Multiple rapid errors → handled gracefully

### Edge Cases to Verify

- Error during page load
- Error while modal already open
- Network disconnect error

### Known Limitations

- Only one error shown at a time (by design)
```

## TypeScript Naming Conventions

```typescript
// API response data
type UserDTO = { id: string; name: string; };

// API request data
type CreateUserSDTO = { name: string; email: string; };

// General type
type UserT = { id: string; name: string; };

// Enum
enum UserRoleE { Admin = 'admin', User = 'user' }

// Component props - ALWAYS named PropsT
type PropsT = { onSubmit: (data: LoginDataT) => void; };
```

## Code Style Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - const + arrow function
export const Component = (props: PropsT) => {
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    props.onClick();
  }, [props.onClick]);

  return <div onClick={handleClick}>{props.title}</div>;
};

// ❌ Wrong - function keyword
export function Component(props: PropsT) { }

// ❌ Wrong - interface
interface PropsT { }

// ❌ Wrong - destructuring props
export const Component = ({ title }: PropsT) => { };
```

## SCSS Mobile-First

```scss
// ✅ Correct - mobile first
.component {
  width: 100%;

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    width: 50%;
  }
}

// ❌ Wrong - desktop first
.component {
  width: 50%;

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

